# Terminal hygiene

1. Short commands (`verify`, one-off scripts) run in the **foreground** with enough `block_until_ms`.
2. **One** dev server — port **3456**. `npm run ui-smoke` starts/stops its own; don’t leave extra `serve` instances.
3. After background work: stop the process; don’t run duplicate smoke/servers; confirm 3456 is free.
4. Reuse shells; don’t open a new one per tiny command.
5. Orphan `serve`/`ui-smoke` cleanup (Windows):

```powershell
Get-CimInstance Win32_Process -Filter "name='node.exe'" |
  Where-Object { $_.CommandLine -match 'serve\\build\\main|run-ui-smoke|ui-smoke-search|run ui-smoke' } |
  ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.ProcessId -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue }
```

Terminal **tabs** are a UI close; kill orphan **processes** after server/smoke work.
